      "content": "i know i'm doing my best but it doesn't change the math. the bills keep coming and the debt just grows. i look at my son's face and i just see the things i can't provide for him. it feels like a mathematical certainty that if i wasn't here, everything would just... ease up. they wouldn't have to worry about how to cover my mistakes anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
